17:38.391 --> 17:40.760
Let's take care
of that right now.

17:40.760 --> 17:43.563
Oh, you're so sweet.

17:43.563 --> 17:45.132
What is that?

17:45.132 --> 17:47.234
Oh, what, this? Oh.

17:47.234 --> 17:49.336
I don't understand,
you're not Jewish.

17:49.336 --> 17:52.472
No, but, um, I've spent
much of my career

17:52.472 --> 17:56.176
working amongst
Jewish people,

17:56.176 --> 17:58.378
and to be honest
since I've met you,

17:58.378 --> 18:00.713
I've taken a great
interest in the faith.

18:00.713 --> 18:03.049
Such a fascinating history,
so much suffering,

18:03.049 --> 18:05.585
and yet such a
love for life.

18:05.585 --> 18:10.157
Which, as I understand
it is what "l'chaim"
means in Hebrew.

18:10.157 --> 18:12.159
Oh.

18:24.003 --> 18:25.738
Hey!

18:25.738 --> 18:27.307
What are you doing out
here by yourself?

18:27.307 --> 18:29.041
Just doing some thinking.

18:29.041 --> 18:30.977
Yeah?

18:30.977 --> 18:32.245
